WorldStage Newsonline– NEM Insurance Plc, a major player in Nigeria’s insurance sector which started business in the country in 1948 through the agency of Edward Turner & Co has released a its financial forecast for the second quarter period ending 30th June 2021 with a projected profit after tax of N2.350 billion which is 37.75% improvement over N1.706 billion projected for Q1 2021. The forecast published at the Nigerian Stock Exchange on Wednesday projected a gross premiums written of N16.320 billion compared with N10.710 billion projection for Q1 2021. WorldStage earlier reported NEM Insurance’s forecast for Q1 2021 with a projected profit after tax of N1.706 billion which is 52.41% of the profit projection for the entire 2020.